        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34042",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is a bug due to a known behavior of sprintf(). See http:\/\/us2.php.net\/manual\/en\/function.sprintf.php#92124 for details. The solution would be to specify a specific precision for sprintf().",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-28T07:09:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-28T07:09:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34045",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lode",
                        "name": "lode",
                        "displayName": "Lode Blomme",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Wouldn't it be possible to detect the precision of the input, and adding this to the sprintf command? Simply increasing the precision would result in added zeros at the end. That's not desirable.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lode",
                        "name": "lode",
                        "displayName": "Lode Blomme",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-28T07:33:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-28T07:35:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34098",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed in r17921. Thank you for taking time to write us!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-31T06:36:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-31T06:36:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34310",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lode",
                        "name": "lode",
                        "displayName": "Lode Blomme",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This solution has the downside of adding trailing zeros to the double value in XML. If you have a message with alot of double values, this can add up to quite some extra data to be tranfered. Therefore I propose an addition to eliminate those trailing zeros :\n\n{code}\nif (strstr($num, '.')) {\n    $num = trim($num, '0');\n    if ($num[0] == '.') {\n        $num = '0' . $num;\n    }\n    if ($num[strlen($num) - 1] == '.') {\n        $num = substr($num, 0, strlen($num) - 1);\n    }\n}\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lode",
                        "name": "lode",
                        "displayName": "Lode Blomme",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-08T07:49:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-08T07:49:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36839",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed in trunk (r19562) and 1.9 release branch (r19563). We now trim trailing \"0\"s when building the XML envelope",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-09T19:39:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-09T19:39:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38516",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=raistlin",
                        "name": "raistlin",
                        "displayName": "Adam Kusmierz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You can't use printf's schema \"f\", bacause it's locale aware. On Windows, this function returns float, but rounded to decimal part (ie. 1 instead 1.123).\r\n\r\nYou should use \"F\" instead:\r\n{code:html|title=Zend\/XmlRpc\/Value\/Double}\r\n49. $formatString = '%1.' . $precision . 'F';\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=raistlin",
                        "name": "raistlin",
                        "displayName": "Adam Kusmierz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-17T10:54:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-17T10:54:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38683",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed in trunk and 1.10 release branch.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-23T09:57:12.000+0000",
